   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER ONE THE DIVINE CREATION OF THE TRIPARTITE MAN BY THE TRIUNE GOD Scripture Reading: Gen 1:26a, 27; 2:7, 9; 3:6-7, 24 OUTLINE According to the image of the Triune God Gen 1:26a, 27: That man may be like God and express God.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>That God's attributes may be expressed in man's virtues.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Creating a spirit for man with His breath of life Gen 2:7: As the organ for man to contact God and receive God.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>As the organ for man to receive God and enjoy God.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Being the tree of life to the tripartite man whom He created Gen 2:9: To be received by man as the life of man.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>That man may live by Him as life in order to live Him out and express Him.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The fall of man: Due to receiving the tree of the knowledge of good and evil, which indicates Satan, the old serpent Gen 3:6.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Corrupting the image that God created for man Gen 3:7.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Losing the position to receive God as life Gen 3:24.</S>
   </TEXT>
